UniFi Network Controller is a centralized management system
for Ubiquiti UniFi products.

You'll need to create a unifi user in order to run with the provided init
script:

# useradd -r -d /var/lib/unifi unifi

You'll also need to add the following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local

if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.unifi ]; then
    /etc/rc.d/rc./unifi start
fi

And the following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown

if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.unifi ]; then
    /etc/rc.d/rc./unifi stop
fi

